(Decision
    "The human author is named 'psyche'. Psyche prompts arrive in natural language; NOTA-formatted persona messages between agents are not psyche; agent-written files are not psyche. Only the psyche is the source of new intent. Intent is primordial — it drives the whole system and has higher authority than every other workspace surface."
    "When I say the psyche, I mean the human, the human driving the machine. So it can only come from a human psyche prompt, a psyche prompt, because there's going to be soon persona is going to have messages are going to be going between agents. And these will be treated differently than a psyche prompt … It'll be easy for the agent to know that this is a human psyche. I'm just going to start saying psyche."
    "Naming the human as psyche; distinguishing psyche prompts (natural language) from upcoming NOTA-formatted persona messages between agents."
    Maximum
    2026-05-19T02:30:00Z)
  (Principle
    "When intent on a question is unclear, absent, or contradicted, ask the psyche for clarification before deciding. Don't infer; don't compose new intent from old; ask. Inferring is the discipline breaking; asking is the discipline working."
    "Let's train the agents to ask for intent clarification. So whenever something doesn't have an intent or the intent isn't clearly specifying what the agent needs to understand, the agent asks for intent clarification. This is an essential skill … Intent is primordial, intent drives the whole system. Intent is what agents need to try to obtain from the side key that drives them."
    "Establishing intent-clarification as a primordial agent discipline; settled into ESSENCE and skills/intent-clarification.md."
    Maximum
    2026-05-19T02:30:00Z)
  (Decision
