    "every repo has one. And it's not, I don't think the intent, the intent is not like the intent protocol with the login. The intent is a little bit like the architecture file in the sense that it's composed, like it's written by the agent, but it's 100% backed by actual intent, actual explicit intent by the author. So everything that goes into an intent file is derived directly with very little, you know, editing in the sense that the agent tries to keep as much as possible to express very much what the author intended to express and doesn't try to like infer more than what the author said or make conclusions or anything like that."
    "Adding per-repo INTENT.md as a second surface in the intent layer; agent-written prose with tight fidelity to psyche statements, no embellishment."
