  (Constraint
    "Inelegant code does not qualify as 'this works'; inelegant tests do not prove that something is broken. Elegance is the criterion for whether agent verification work is done and for whether a falsification result is load-bearing. Passing tests on ugly code do not finish the work; failing inelegant tests do not prove the code under test is broken."
    "… inelegant code does not qualify as 'this works' and inelegant tests does not prove that something is necessarily broken"
